---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Why not just use LangChain?",
    a: "Plynf is infrastructure under your agent, not a framework. LangChain composes prompts. Plynf manages the runtime: workspace state, tool gateway, identity, coordination. Use both if you want.",
  },
  {
    q: "Why not Temporal?",
    a: "Temporal is excellent at durable execution. Plynf includes that plus workspace state, tool gateway, identity, and 8 OAuth providers. Agent-aware. Packaged as one coherent surface, rather than five tools you have to stitch together.",
  },
  {
    q: "Self-hosted or cloud?",
    a: "Self-hosted today. One command from a clean clone. Hosted SaaS in beta soon. The self-hosted build is and will always be Apache 2.0.",
  },
  {
    q: "Which LLM does it use?",
    a: "Bring your own. Anthropic, OpenAI, local models, or our Mock provider for tests. Plynf is the substrate; the model is your choice.",
  },
  {
    q: "What about data privacy?",
    a: "Self-hosted means your data never leaves your machine. Full stop. Cloud (when live) will be SOC 2 in progress, with a DPA on the Enterprise tier.",
  },
  {
    q: "Is it production-ready?",
    a: "v1.5 ships with 2,867 tests, multi-region scaffolding, a Postgres backend, k8s/Helm/Terraform deploy artifacts, and a published threat model. First production deploys are this quarter.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's the license?",
    a: "Apache 2.0. Use it, fork it, embed it. The only thing we ask is keep the upstream attribution.",
  },
  {
    q: "How do I get help?",
    a: "GitHub issues for OSS. Email response within 24h on Pro. Dedicated Slack channel on Enterprise. We answer every issue, every time.",
  },
];
---

<section class="section" id="faq">
  <div class="container-page" data-reveal>
    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] lg:gap-16">
      <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-24 self-start">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">FAQ</p>
        <h2 class="section-title text-balance">
          Honest answers to the questions buyers actually ask.
        </h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Still have one? <a href="mailto:hello@plynf.com" class="text-ink-primary underline underline-offset-4 decoration-border-strong hover:decoration-accent">Email us</a> or open a
          <a href="https://github.com/nico-schindlbeck-jpg/plinth/discussions" class="text-ink-primary underline underline-offset-4 decoration-border-strong hover:decoration-accent">discussion</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="divide-y divide-border border-y border-border">
        {
          faqs.map((item, i) => (
            <li>
              <details class="group" open={i === 0}>
                <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-start gap-4 py-5 list-none select-none">
                  <span class="mt-1 flex h-6 w-6 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-border bg-bg-2 text-ink-muted transition-colors group-hover:text-ink-primary group-open:bg-accent group-open:text-[#190612] group-open:border-accent">
                    <svg class="h-3 w-3 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true">
                      <path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"></path>
                    </svg>
                  </span>
                  <span class="flex-1 text-base font-medium text-ink-primary group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">
                    {item.q}
                  </span>
                </summary>
                <div class="pb-5 pl-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
                  {item.a}
                </div>
              </details>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
